episodes.title: Freedom 45?
episodes.plot: Ricky, Julian, and bubbles have the park in good hands and everything seems to be going well, until Barbara and her gang come back from jail looking to regain the park.

episodes.title: You Want the Lot Fees, Suck Them Out of the Tip of My Cock
episodes.plot: Desperate for cash to fight the impending court case, the boys try to collect outstanding lot fees at the park and consider a return to petty crime.

episodes.title: A Three Tiered Shit Dyke
episodes.plot: As Barb and her crew try to bully Lahey and Randy into testifying for her in court the boys set out to case a fancy neighborhood.

episodes.title: Shit Covered Cave Teeth
episodes.plot: After handing over Trinity's wedding money. Ricky swears off crime but Julian has other plans.

episodes.title: If You Don't Believe It, It's Not Real
episodes.plot: When a scheme goes awry the boys turn to Sam the caveman for help.

episodes.title: All the Fuckin Dope You Can Smoke
episodes.plot: Julian turns his bar into a casino, the ad made up by the the boys stirs up trouble and gets some celebrity attention.

episodes.title: Up in Smoke We Go
episodes.plot: Snoop Dogg and his crew rock up at Sunnyvale Trailer Park for a visit.

episodes.title: The Super Bling Cowboy
episodes.plot: Bubbles suffers from a bad case of nerves at his open mic night.

episodes.title: Thugged Out Gangsta Shit
episodes.plot: Tom sets out on an adventure with Lucy, while Snoop tries Ricky's new concoction and Lahey plots a diabolical mission.

episodes.title: Looks Like the Liquor Wins
episodes.plot: The venue for Trinity's wedding is changed to the hospital so Ricky can be there, even though he remains in a coma. Mr. Lahey reveals the secret Barb had been blackmailing him with and Barb and Julian each have tough decisions to make regarding the Park and their roles in both its history and its future.
